<recipe>
<title>
Slow Cooker Cilantro Lime Chicken
</title>
<details>
AUTHOR: I Heart Eating
PREP TIME: 10 minutes
COOK TIME: 7 hours 30 minutes
TOTAL TIME: 7 hours 40 minutes
COURSE: Main Course
CUISINE: Mexican
KEYWORD: chicken, slow cooker
SERVINGS: 12 servings
</details>
<ingredients>
1 small yellow or white onion
4 lbs . boneless skinless chicken breast
1/2 c . fresh lime juice about 3-4 limes
2 T . olive oil
Salt and pepper
1 small bunch cilantro
</ingredients>
<instructions>
Dice onion, and place in the bottom of slow cooker.
Add chicken on top of onion.
Stir together lime juice and olive oil.
Pour over chicken.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Place cilantro over chicken.
Cover, and cook on low for 7-8 hours, or until chicken shreds easily.
Remove chicken to plate.
Turn slow cooker to WARM.
Puree sauce, and return to slow cooker.
Shred chicken, and place back in sauce in slow cooker.
Cover, and let sit in sauce for about 20-30 minutes.
</instructions>
</recipe>
